Design the correct DI pattern for a NetworkService shared across 10+ screens using @Observable and @Environment:

```swift
protocol NetworkServiceProtocol {
    func fetch<T: Decodable>(_ url: URL) async throws -> T
}

// How should this be registered in Environment and consumed by ViewModels?
```

evals.expected_output:
Three-step @Entry pattern: (1) Register a default value using @Entry in an EnvironmentValues extension:

```swift
extension EnvironmentValues {
    @Entry var networkService: NetworkServiceProtocol = LiveNetworkService()
}
```

(2) Override at the root for production or testing:
```swift
ContentView().environment(\.networkService, LiveNetworkService())
// In tests: .environment(\.networkService, MockNetworkService())
```

(3) View reads from environment and passes to ViewModel init:
```swift
struct ItemView: View {
    @Environment(\.networkService) var networkService
    @State private var viewModel: ItemViewModel

    init() { } // viewModel initialized in .task or with environment value
}
```

This enables test injection without changing any ViewModel code.

