evals.expected_output:
ItemViewModel is @MainActor — accessing its properties from a non-@MainActor context is a compile error in Swift 6 (or a concurrency warning in Swift 5). Fix: mark the entire test class @MainActor:

```swift
@MainActor
class ItemViewModelTests: XCTestCase {
    ...
}
```

This ensures all test methods run on the main actor, matching the ViewModel's isolation context. Individual methods can be marked async if needed for await calls.

